  "texts": [
    "Based on techniques developped of Honorio and Jaakkola (2014) and Bégin et al. (2016), Alquier and Guedj (2018) proved inequalities similar to PAC-Bayes bounds, that hold for heavy-tailed losses (they can also hold for non i.i.d.",
    "losses, we will discuss this point later).",
    "Curiously, these bounds depend no longer on the Kullback-Leibler divergence, but on other divergences.",
    "An example of such an inequality is provided here and relies only on the assumption that the losses have a variance.",
    "We recall a notation from Section 3: V(θ) = Var(ℓ i (θ))."
